      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "cef8983c8b5bf51b58df23a779769cc4b8ca8db5",
            "subject": "LU-8497 osp: handle remote -ENOMEM from osp_send_update_req()"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Thomas Stibor",
          "email": "t.stibor@gsi.de",
          "date": "2017-11-17 14:31:39.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-12-01 05:16:46.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-10256 hsm: enable setting archive_id in hsm_set",
        "message": "LU-10256 hsm: enable setting archive_id in hsm_set\n\nSetting HSM flags in lfs_hsm_change_flags(...,LFS_HSM_SET)\ndoes not allow to specify the archive_id, that is,\nin llapi_hsm_state_set(path, mask, 0, 0 /* archive_id */)\narchive_id = 0 is always set, which means no identifier change.\nFor having full flexibility (e.g. for debugging), introduce\nthe additional option --archive-id in hsm_set. If the option\nis not provided, the default behavior (archive_id = 0) is used\nand no archive identifier change is done. In addition a\ntest case is provided to check the functionality and shell\nfunction get_hsm_archive_id() is modified in favor of more\nrobust grep for contents after pattern approach.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-hsm\nSigned-off-by: Thomas Stibor <t.stibor@gsi.de>\nChange-Id: I2145a18ecf32479527bb045140e5e881e58dd115\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/30150\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Stephan Thiell <sthiell@stanford.edu>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
